PN,37301
SC,0001
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F373A1781874674
OL,3,CThousands of shoplifting crimes
OL,4,Ccommitted by 104 repeat offenders
OL,6,FBritain's biggest police force is
OL,7,Fpushing for fast-track courts for
OL,8,Fshoplifters as it revealed that 104
OL,9,Frepeat offenders were responsible for
OL,10,Fmore than 5,300 crimes in the past two
OL,11,Fyears.
OL,13,FEach of the re-offenders broke the law
OL,14,Fat least 31 times before they were
OL,15,Fjailed.
OL,17,FFast-track courts typically hear cases
OL,18,Fin a single day, which allows for
OL,19,Fquicker resolutions to cases.
OL,1,W h7}h7}j7}h7}h7}                 G1/13
OL,2,W+,"-'*%/*-'"-'*%/T(,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BLondon NewsCThis Day FReg TV
FL,374,370,120,260,000,100
PN,37302
SC,0002
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F373A1781874674
OL,3,CThousands of shoplifting crimes
OL,4,Ccommitted by 104 repeat offenders
OL,6,FThe Metropolitan Police said serial
OL,7,Fcriminals were behind 4,389
OL,8,Fshoplifting offences and another 1,000
OL,9,Fother crimes over the past two
OL,10,Ffinancial years.
OL,12,FShoplifting offences made up around a
OL,13,Fthird of cases in London where a
OL,14,Fsuspect has been identified.
OL,16,FAll bar three of the criminals
OL,17,Fcontinued offending after they had
OL,18,Fbeen charged.
OL,20,FAssistant Commissioner Matt Twist said:
OL,1,W h7}h7}j7}h7}h7}                 G2/13
OL,2,W+,"-'*%/*-'"-'*%/T(,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BLondon NewsCThis Day FReg TV
FL,374,370,120,260,000,100
PN,37303
SC,0003
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F373A1781874674
OL,3,CThousands of shoplifting crimes
OL,4,Ccommitted by 104 repeat offenders
OL,6,F"We know we haven't always got the
OL,7,Fresponse to retail crime right.
OL,9,F"Over the past 18 months, we have
OL,10,Fchanged that, giving neighbourhood
OL,11,Fofficers new technology to quickly
OL,12,Fidentify and arrest the small number
OL,13,Fof offenders responsible for a
OL,14,Fdisproportionate amount of crime.
OL,16,F"Working hand-in-hand with retailers
OL,17,Fand sharing evidence has been crucial
OL,18,Fin building strong cases and securing
OL,19,Fcharges.
OL,26,@nD@AOUxD@AOU
OL,1,W h7}h7}j7}h7}h7}                 G3/13
OL,2,W+,"-'*%/*-'"-'*%/T(,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BLondon NewsCThis Day FReg TV
FL,374,370,120,260,000,100
PN,37304
SC,0004
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F373A1781874674
OL,3,CThousands of shoplifting crimes
OL,4,Ccommitted by 104 repeat offenders
OL,6,F"Where underreporting remains, we are
OL,7,Fworking with businesses to ensure
OL,8,Fincidents are reported to bring those
OL,9,Foffenders to justice.
OL,11,F"Whilst we recognise the #5 million
OL,12,Ffrom Government to disrupt organised
OL,13,Fretail crime, we are still seeing the
OL,14,Fsame individuals come back again and
OL,15,Fagain ` that shows the system needs to
OL,16,Fchange.
OL,18,F"That's why we are calling on the Home
OL,19,FOffice and Ministry of Justice to take
OL,20,Faction, and we stand ready to help
OL,21,Fbreak this cycle for good."
OL,26,@sD@AOU}D@[O]
OL,1,W h7}h7}j7}h7}h7}                 G4/13
OL,2,W+,"-'*%/*-'"-'*%/T(,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BLondon NewsCThis Day FReg TV
FL,374,370,120,260,000,100
PN,37305
SC,0005
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F373A1781874674
OL,3,CThousands of shoplifting crimes
OL,4,Ccommitted by 104 repeat offenders
OL,6,FThe Metropolitan Police's crime data
OL,7,Fwebsite shared that only 6.8% of
OL,8,Fshoplifting cases in the year up to
OL,9,FMay 2025 had a positive outcome.
OL,10,FThat's 6939 cases out of 101,924.
OL,12,FA positive outcome includes a charge
OL,13,For summons, a caution, the offender
OL,14,Fdying, a penalty notice or cannabis
OL,15,Fwarning being issued, a community
OL,16,Fresolution or where the offence is
OL,17,Ftaken into account with other crimes.
OL,1,W h7}h7}j7}h7}h7}                 G5/13
OL,2,W+,"-'*%/*-'"-'*%/T(,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BLondon NewsCThis Day FReg TV
FL,374,370,120,260,000,100
PN,37306
SC,0006
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F373A1781874674
OL,3,CThousands of shoplifting crimes
OL,4,Ccommitted by 104 repeat offenders
OL,6,FIn the year to May 2026, cases with a
OL,7,Fpositive outcome rose to 14.3%. That's
OL,8,F14,347 offences out of a total of
OL,9,F100,264.
OL,11,FHelen Dickinson, chief executive of
OL,12,Fthe British Retail Consortium, said
OL,13,Fthat although police and retailers are
OL,14,Fworking together, "too many offenders
OL,15,Fstill face little meaningful
OL,16,Fconsequence".
OL,26,@vD@SOUxD@LO]
OL,1,W h7}h7}j7}h7}h7}                 G6/13
OL,2,W+,"-'*%/*-'"-'*%/T(,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BLondon NewsCThis Day FReg TV
FL,374,370,120,260,000,100
PN,37307
SC,0007
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F373A1781874674
OL,3,CThousands of shoplifting crimes
OL,4,Ccommitted by 104 repeat offenders
OL,6,FShe continued: "To truly turn the tide
OL,7,Fon retail crime, Government must
OL,8,Fstrengthen the justice system so
OL,9,Foffenders, particularly repeat
OL,10,Foffenders, are brought to justice
OL,11,Fquickly and effectively.
OL,13,F"These are not victimless crimes `
OL,14,Fthey have a devastating impact on
OL,15,Fretail workers, businesses and
OL,16,Fcommunities."
OL,26,@nD@POUxD@MO]
OL,1,W h7}h7}j7}h7}h7}                 G7/13
OL,2,W+,"-'*%/*-'"-'*%/T(,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BLondon NewsCThis Day FReg TV
FL,374,370,120,260,000,100
PN,37308
SC,0008
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F373A1781874674
OL,3,CThousands of shoplifting crimes
OL,4,Ccommitted by 104 repeat offenders
OL,6,FThe Met, British Retail Consortium and
OL,7,FRetail Trust have jointly written to
OL,8,Fthe Home Office and Ministry of
OL,9,FJustice to call for fast-track courts
OL,10,Fso repeat offenders appear within 72
OL,11,Fhours of charge.
OL,13,FThey want a clearer escalation system
OL,14,Ffor people who keep breaching criminal
OL,15,Fbehaviour orders, and more consistent
OL,16,Fenforcement of the orders.
OL,18,FDee Corsi, New West End Company chief
OL,19,Fexecutive, said there is a difference
OL,20,Fbetween opportunistic shop thieves and
OL,21,Fthose who repeatedly target stores:
OL,1,W h7}h7}j7}h7}h7}                 G8/13
OL,2,W+,"-'*%/*-'"-'*%/T(,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BLondon NewsCThis Day FReg TV
FL,374,370,120,260,000,100
PN,37309
SC,0009
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F373A1781874674
OL,3,CThousands of shoplifting crimes
OL,4,Ccommitted by 104 repeat offenders
OL,6,F"Retail crime cannot be tackled
OL,7,Fthrough enforcement measures alone,
OL,8,Fand businesses are rightly looking for
OL,9,Fthe justice system to take a more
OL,10,Frobust approach to those who
OL,11,Fsystematically target high street
OL,12,Fshops.
OL,14,F"There is a vast gulf between
OL,15,Fopportunistic shoplifting and retail
OL,16,Fcrime perpetrated by prolific
OL,17,Foffenders and organised groups.
OL,26,@nD@AOUvD@AOU
OL,1,W h7}h7}j7}h7}h7}                 G9/13
OL,2,W+,"-'*%/*-'"-'*%/T(,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BLondon NewsCThis Day FReg TV
FL,374,370,120,260,000,100
PN,37310
SC,0010
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F373A1781874674
OL,3,CThousands of shoplifting crimes
OL,4,Ccommitted by 104 repeat offenders
OL,6,F"It is time that those responsible for
OL,7,Fprolific and organised offending face
OL,8,Fconsequences which reflect the scale
OL,9,Fof harm caused to businesses and
OL,10,Ffrontline staff."
OL,12,FChris Brook-Carter, chief executive of
OL,13,Fthe Retail Trust, said:
OL,15,F"Theft and assaults can have a
OL,16,Fdevastating impact on people's lives
OL,17,Fand damage their confidence, wellbeing
OL,18,Fand sense of safety long after their
OL,19,Fretail shifts have finished.
OL,26,@rD@QO]wD@AOU
OL,1,W h7}h7}j7}h7}h7}                G10/13
OL,2,W+,"-'*%/*-'"-'*%/T(,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BLondon NewsCThis Day FReg TV
FL,374,370,120,260,000,100
PN,37311
SC,0011
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F373A1781874674
OL,3,CThousands of shoplifting crimes
OL,4,Ccommitted by 104 repeat offenders
OL,6,F"Shop workers need to see every
OL,7,Fincident taken seriously and receive
OL,8,Fthe right support afterwards so they
OL,9,Fare not left to deal with the
OL,10,Fconsequences on their own.
OL,12,F"The Retail Trust is working with
OL,13,Fpolice forces and hundreds of
OL,14,Fretailers across the country to make
OL,15,Fit easier for people to report crime
OL,16,Fand abuse and get more help to feel
OL,17,Fsafer at work.
OL,26,@nD@AOUtD@AOU
OL,1,W h7}h7}j7}h7}h7}                G11/13
OL,2,W+,"-'*%/*-'"-'*%/T(,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BLondon NewsCThis Day FReg TV
FL,374,370,120,260,000,100
PN,37312
SC,0012
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F373A1781874674
OL,3,CThousands of shoplifting crimes
OL,4,Ccommitted by 104 repeat offenders
OL,6,F"These new laws will strengthen our
OL,7,Fefforts to protect retail workers by
OL,8,Fensuring those who repeatedly target
OL,9,Fshops and intimidate staff face swift
OL,10,Fand serious consequences."
OL,12,FA government spokesperson said
OL,13,Fshoplifting "devastates high streets
OL,14,Fand hollows out businesses".
OL,16,F"That's why we're taking tough action
OL,17,Fto turn the tide on the epidemic of
OL,18,Fshop theft," they said.
OL,26,@nD@AOUrD@ZO]uD@MOUvD@[O]xD@AOUzD@LO]
OL,1,W h7}h7}j7}h7}h7}                G12/13
OL,2,W+,"-'*%/*-'"-'*%/T(,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BLondon NewsCThis Day FReg TV
FL,374,370,120,260,000,100
PN,37313
SC,0013
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F373A1781874674
OL,3,CThousands of shoplifting crimes
OL,4,Ccommitted by 104 repeat offenders
OL,6,F"Charge volumes are up 17%, we're
OL,7,Fspeeding up court delays and scrapping
OL,8,Fthe so-called #200 'licence to steal'
OL,9,Fso that shoplifters can be prosecuted."
OL,26,@nD@AOUqD@gO]
OL,1,W h7}h7}j7}h7}h7}                G13/13
